abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump said on Tuesday that Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu told him the Trump administration's proposed plan for Middle East peace would be a basis for direct negotiations.
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump said on Tuesday that Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu told him the Trump administration's proposed plan for Middle East peace would be a basis for direct negotiations.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. President Donald Trump said on Tuesday that Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu told him the Trump administration's proposed plan for Middle East peace would be a basis for direct negotiations.
headline_main: Netanyahu Says Peace Plan Would Be Base for Negotiations: Trump
headline_print_headline: Netanyahu Says Peace Plan Would Be Base for Negotiations: Trump

abstract: Lawyers defending U.S. President Donald Trump in his Senate impeachment trial wrap up their presentation on Tuesday.
snippet: Lawyers defending U.S. President Donald Trump in his Senate impeachment trial wrap up their presentation on Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Lawyers defending U.S. President Donald Trump in his Senate impeachment trial wrap up their presentation on Tuesday.

abstract: A group of Iranian lawmakers on Tuesday asked parliament to debate a motion for Iran to quit a treaty governing global nuclear arms control, a move apparently aimed at pressuring European powers to salvage Tehran's own 2015 nuclear deal.
snippet: A group of Iranian lawmakers on Tuesday asked parliament to debate a motion for Iran to quit a treaty governing global nuclear arms control, a move apparently aimed at pressuring European powers to salvage Tehran's own 2015 nuclear deal.
lead_paragraph: DUBAI — A group of Iranian lawmakers on Tuesday asked parliament to debate a motion for Iran to quit a treaty governing global nuclear arms control, a move apparently aimed at pressuring European powers to salvage Tehran's own 2015 nuclear deal.
headline_main: Iran Lawmakers Call for Debate on Quitting Nuclear Arms Treaty
headline_print_headline: Iran Lawmakers Call for Debate on Quitting Nuclear Arms Treaty

abstract: U.S. Senate Democratic leader Chuck Schumer on Tuesday rejected a proposal from a couple of Republican senators that lawmakers view a book manuscript produced by a former adviser to President Donald Trump in a classified setting, saying nothing can substitute for sworn testimony.
snippet: U.S. Senate Democratic leader Chuck Schumer on Tuesday rejected a proposal from a couple of Republican senators that lawmakers view a book manuscript produced by a former adviser to President Donald Trump in a classified setting, saying nothing ca...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. Senate Democratic leader Chuck Schumer on Tuesday rejected a proposal from a couple of Republican senators that lawmakers view a book manuscript produced by a former adviser to President Donald Trump in a classified setting, saying nothing can substitute for sworn testimony.
headline_main: Democrat Schumer Calls Proposal to Peruse Bolton Manuscript in Private 'Absurd'
headline_print_headline: Democrat Schumer Calls Proposal to Peruse Bolton Manuscript in Private 'Absurd'

abstract: Republican U.S. Senator Lindsey Graham on Tuesday said he would support a plan making former national security adviser John Bolton's book manuscript available for senators to review as they weigh President Donald Trump's impeachment.
snippet: Republican U.S. Senator Lindsey Graham on Tuesday said he would support a plan making former national security adviser John Bolton's book manuscript available for senators to review as they weigh President Donald Trump's impeachment.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Republican U.S. Senator Lindsey Graham on Tuesday said he would support a plan making former national security adviser John Bolton's book manuscript available for senators to review as they weigh President Donald Trump's impeachment.
headline_main: Sen. Graham Backs Plan to Make Bolton Manuscript Available to Senators
headline_print_headline: Sen. Graham Backs Plan to Make Bolton Manuscript Available to Senators

abstract: When U.S. presidential candidate Joe Biden went to an Iowa university to campaign this week, one thing was in short supply: students who support him.
snippet: When U.S. presidential candidate Joe Biden went to an Iowa university to campaign this week, one thing was in short supply: students who support him.
lead_paragraph: CEDAR FALLS, Iowa — When U.S. presidential candidate Joe Biden went to an Iowa university to campaign this week, one thing was in short supply: students who support him.
headline_main: Biden's Final Iowa Drive Sweeps Through Rival Territory
headline_print_headline: Biden's Final Iowa Drive Sweeps Through Rival Territory

abstract: “That manuscript is pertinent and we should get access to that manuscript to see what they’re actually saying,” Senator James Lankford said.
snippet: “That manuscript is pertinent and we should get access to that manuscript to see what they’re actually saying,” Senator James Lankford said.
lead_paragraph: Two Republican senators are backing a proposal to make the manuscript of John Bolton’s forthcoming book available in a classified setting to all members of the Senate, an idea some Republicans are considering as they grapple with a new account by the former national security adviser that corroborates a central piece of the impeachment case against President Trump.

abstract: Readers react to Bret Stephens’s argument that the Democrats’ far-left candidates are as “reckless” as the president, leaving “none of the above” as a viable option.

abstract: In normal years, Iowa is the center of the political universe during the final stretch before its famed caucuses. Top candidates rumble across the state on multi-city bus tours and hold giant rallies every night. Images of the state's snowy landscape flood television screens.
snippet: In normal years, Iowa is the center of the political universe during the final stretch before its famed caucuses. Top candidates rumble across the state on multi-city bus tours and hold giant rallies every night. Images of the state's snowy landsc...
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — In normal years, Iowa is the center of the political universe during the final stretch before its famed caucuses. Top candidates rumble across the state on multi-city bus tours and hold giant rallies every night. Images of the state's snowy landscape flood television screens.
headline_main: Iowans Adjust to 'Weird' Final Days of Caucus Campaign

abstract: Just kidding. The creator of the acclaimed sitcom, Michael Schur, discusses political parallels, silly tortures and what the show had to say about “the impossibility of being alive.”
snippet: Just kidding. The creator of the acclaimed sitcom, Michael Schur, discusses political parallels, silly tortures and what the show had to say about “the impossibility of being alive.”
lead_paragraph: Michael Schur swears he didn’t name Michael, the avuncular architect played by Ted Danson on Schur’s metaphysical sitcom, “The Good Place,” after himself. The character was actually based on St. Michael the Archangel, who according to Christian tradition is involved in the final judgment of souls.
